      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data field defines the authorization date of the pending transaction. It is a 6-byte alphanumeric field (PIC X(06)) that stores the date when the authorization was requested. The format of the date is not specified within the copybook but would be defined by the calling program. This field is part of the larger pending authorization request structure defined in this copybook. The value of this field is likely used for reporting, auditing, and reconciliation purposes. The field itself does not perform any logic or call any other programs; it simply holds the authorization date value.",
